OL,3,CChiltern Railways recovers #12,000
OL,4,Cfrom persistent fare dodger
OL,6,FA train operator said it has recovered
OL,7,F#12,000 from a habitual fare dodger
OL,8,Fwho offended 736 times.
OL,10,FChiltern Railways which serves Oxford,
OL,11,FAylesbury and Bicester, said the
OL,12,Fculprit, who it did not name,
OL,13,Fcommitted instances of "fraudulent
OL,14,Freclaims of money, knowingly not
OL,15,Fpaying the correct fare and railcard
OL,16,Fabuse".
OL,18,FA total of 8,064 cases were reported
OL,19,Ffor investigation by Chiltern's
OL,20,Feconomic crime, fraud and prosecutions
OL,21,Funit last year.
